{"title_page": "Government Intermediate College, Khirerikhal", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2017}}[https://schools.org.in/garhwal/05061311102/govt.-inter-college-khirerikhal.html Government Intermediate College]\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=January 2017}}\n{{Underlinked|date=February 2017}}\n}}\nThe '''Government Intermediate College, Khirerikhal''' is one of the oldest and largest intermediate schools in the Nainidanda Block of [[Pauri District]], [[Uttarakhand]]. The School was founded in early 1975 and is fully managed and funded by the state government. It offers classes from 6th to 12th (upper primary/higher secondary). It is a [[co-educational]] school and has a capacity of 550 students.\n\n==External links==\n*https://schools.org.in/garhwal/05061311102/govt.-inter-college-khirerikhal.html\n\n{{coord missing|Uttarakhand}}https://alchetron.com/Government-Intermediate-College,-Khirerikhal\n\n[[Category:Government schools in India]]\n[[Category:Junior colleges in India]]\n[[Category:High schools and secondary schools in Uttarakhand]]\n[[Category:Pauri Garhwal district]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1975]]\n[[Category:1975 establishments in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2017}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=January 2017}}\n{{Underlinked|date=February 2017}}\n}}\nThe '''Government Intermediate College, Khirerikhal''' is one of the oldest and largest intermediate schools in the Nainidanda Block of [[Pauri District]], [[Uttarakhand]]. The School was founded in early 1975 and is fully managed and funded by the state government. It offers classes from 6th to 12th (upper primary/higher secondary). It is a [[co-educational]] school and has a capacity of 550 students.\n\n==External links==\n*[https://schools.org.in/garhwal/05061311102/govt.-inter-college-khirerikhal.html]\n\n{{coord missing|Uttarakhand}}\n\n[[Category:Government schools in India]]\n[[Category:Junior colleges in India]]\n[[Category:High schools and secondary schools in Uttarakhand]]\n[[Category:Pauri Garhwal district]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1975]]\n[[Category:1975 establishments in India]]\n", "name_user": "Sidhichawla", "label": "safe", "comment": "I have added wikipedia link and some external links related to the given article.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_Intermediate_College,_Khirerikhal"}
{"title_page": "David Lynch filmography", "text_new": "{{David Lynch sidebar}}\n[[File:David Lynch at Town Hall.jpg|right|thumb|upright|alt=A man standing at a lectern, delivering a speech|Lynch, speaking in 2007]]\n\n[[David Lynch|David Keith Lynch]] (born January&nbsp;20, 1946) is an American [[filmmaker]], [[television director]], [[visual artist]], musician and occasional actor. Known for his [[surrealism|surrealist]] films, he has developed his own unique cinematic style which has been dubbed \"Lynchian\"{{sfn|Rodley|Lynch|2005|pp=109 & 192}} and is characterized by its dream imagery and meticulous [[sound design]]. The surreal and, in many cases, violent elements to his films have earned them the reputation that they \"disturb, offend or mystify\" their audiences.{{sfn|Rodley|Lynch|2005|p=245}}\n\nLynch's [[wikt:oeuvre|oeuvre]] includes short and feature-length films, music videos, documentaries and television episodes, while his involvement in these ranges from direction, production and screenwriting to acting and sound design. Lynch's first project was the 1967 short ''[[Six Men Getting Sick (Six Times)]]'', an animated film which blended elements of sculpture and painting into its animation.{{sfn|Odell|Le Blanc|2007|pp=19\u201320}} His first feature-length project, 1977's ''[[Eraserhead]]'', became a [[cult film]] and launched his commercial career.{{sfn|Odell|Le Blanc|2007|p=31}} It also marked his first collaboration with [[Jack Nance]], an actor who would appear in many more of Lynch's productions until his death in 1996.{{sfn|Odell|Le Blanc|2007|p=129}} Lynch's other feature films include the critically successful ''[[The Elephant Man (film)|The Elephant Man]]'' (1980), ''[[Blue Velvet (film)|Blue Velvet]]'' (1986) and ''[[Mulholland Drive (film)|Mulholland Drive]]'' (2001), all of which went on to earn [[Academy Award]] nominations,<ref name=\"oscar 2002\">{{cite web |url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/2002 |title=74th Academy Awards Winners {{!}} Oscar Legacy |publisher=[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] |accessdate=August 13, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"oscar 1987\">{{cite web |url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1987 |title=59th Academy Awards Winners {{!}} Oscar Legacy |publisher=[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] |accessdate=August 13, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"oscar 1980\">{{cite web |url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1981 |title=53rd Academy Awards Winners {{!}} Oscar Legacy |publisher=[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] |accessdate=August 13, 2012}}</ref> and the commercial flop ''[[Dune (1984 film)|Dune]]''.{{sfn|Odell|Le Blanc|2007|p=51}}\n\nLynch has also branched out into television, and later, internet-based series. His first foray into the medium was ''[[Twin Peaks]]'', a joint venture with [[Mark Frost]]. ''Twin Peaks'' became a cult success,{{sfn|Odell|Le Blanc|2007|pp=69\u201374}} leading to Lynch and Frost working together on a number of other projects, including ''[[On the Air (TV series)|On the Air]]''{{sfn|Odell|Le Blanc|2007|pp=17}} and ''[[American Chronicles]]''.{{sfn|Odell|Le Blanc|2007|pp=105\u2013106}} In 2002 Lynch began producing two series of shorts released through his official website: the [[Adobe Flash|Flash]]-animated ''[[DumbLand]]''{{sfn|Odell|Le Blanc|2007|p=136}} and ''[[Rabbits (film)|Rabbits]]''.{{sfn|Odell|Le Blanc|2007|p=117}} Having begun acting in his 1972 short ''The Amputee'',{{sfn|Odell|Le Blanc|2007|p=130}} Lynch went on to appear on-camera in ''Twin Peaks'',<ref name=\"bfi\">{{cite web |url=http://ftvdb.bfi.org.uk/sift/individual/82558?view=credit |title=BFI {{!}} Film & TV Database {{!}} Lynch, David |publisher=[[British Film Institute]] |accessdate=August 13, 2012}}</ref> ''[[Zelly and Me]]'' and ''Dune''.<ref name=\"allrovi\">{{cite web |url=https://www.allmovie.com/artist/david-lynch-p100454/ |title=David Lynch movies, photos, movie reviews, filmography, and biography |work=[[AllMovie]] |publisher=[[Allrovi]] |first=Jason |last= Ankeny |accessdate=August 13, 2012}}</ref> From 2007, Lynch has appeared in a recurring voice role in the animated series ''[[The Cleveland Show]]''.<ref name=\"tvguide\"/>\n\n==Feature films==\n===As director===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:65px;\" | Director\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:65px;\" | Writer\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:65px;\" | Producer\n! scope=\"col\" | Notes\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:50px;\" | Ref(s)\n|-\n| 1977\n| ''[[Eraserhead]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| Also editor, composer, art director, and special effects\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"allrovi\"/>\n|-\n| 1980\n| ''[[The Elephant Man (film)|The Elephant Man]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| Also musical director and sound designer;<br/>Co-written with Christopher De Vore and [[Eric Bergren]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"allrovi\"/>\n|-\n| 1984\n| ''[[Dune (1984 film)|Dune]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"allrovi\"/>\n|-\n| 1986\n| ''[[Blue Velvet (film)|Blue Velvet]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"allrovi\"/>\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''[[Wild at Heart (film)|Wild at Heart]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"allrovi\"/>\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''[[Twin Peaks: Fire Walk with Me]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes|Executive}}\n| Also sound designer;<br/>Co-written with [[Robert Engels]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"allrovi\"/>\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''[[Lost Highway (film)|Lost Highway]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| Also sound designer;<br/>Co-written with [[Barry Gifford]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"allrovi\"/>\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[The Straight Story]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| Also sound designer\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref n