do looks directly at the camera, slightly smiling|''Twin Peaks'' earned several nominations at the [[42nd Primetime Emmy Awards]] ''(Lynch pictured at the ceremony)''.]]\n\n[[File:Naomi Watts \u00e9s David Lynch--.jpg|right|thumb|alt=A blonde woman and a grey-haired man, holding hands and smiling|Lynch has worked with [[Naomi Watts]] on several projects, including ''[[Rabbits (film)|Rabbits]]'' and ''[[Mulholland Drive (film)|Mulholland Drive]]''.]]\n\n===Television series===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Series\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Director\n! scope=\"col\" | Writer\n! scope=\"col\" | Producer\n! scope=\"col\" | Other\n! scope=\"col\" | Notes\n! scope=\"col\" | Ref(s)\n|-\n| ''[[Twin Peaks]]''\n| 1990\u20131991 ([[American Broadcasting Corporation|ABC]])\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes|Executive}}\n| {{yes}}\n| Co-created with [[Mark Frost]]<br/>Director (6 episodes)<br/>Writer (4 episodes)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"allrovi\"/>\n|-\n| ''[[American Chronicles]]''\n| 1990 ([[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]])\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| Episode: \"Champions\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{sfn|Barney|2009|p=xxvi}}\n|-\n| ''[[On the Air (TV series)|On the Air]]''\n| 1992 ([[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]])\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes|Executive}}\n| {{yes}}\n| Co-created with Mark Frost<br/>Director (Episode: \"The Lester Guy Show\")<br/>Writer (2 episodes)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{sfn|Barney|2009|p=xxvi}}\n|-\n| ''[[Hotel Room]]''\n| 1993 ([[HBO]])\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes|Executive}}\n| {{yes}}\n| Co-created with [[Monty Montgomery (producer)|Monty Montgomery]]<br/>Director (2 episodes)<br/>Also sound designer\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{sfn|Barney|2009|p=xxvi}}\n|-\n| ''[[Twin Peaks (season 3)|Twin Peaks]]''\n| 2017 ([[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]])\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes|Executive}}\n| {{yes}}\n| Co-created with Mark Frost<br/>A